3=User:Immanuelle/Haibutsu Kishaku|13=User:Immanuelle/Haibutsu kishaku|qq=}}, it was enshrined at Isurugi shrines nationwide after being invited from {{ill|Sagami Province|ja|相模国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sagami Province|qq=}} and {{ill|Amefuriyama Daisanji|ja|大山寺 (伊勢原市)|lt=Amefuriyama Daisanji|lt_ja=雨降山大山寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amefuriyama Daisanji|qq=}} via {{ill|Invitation|ja|勧請|lt=Enshrinement|1=Kanjō|2=ja|3=分霊|4=es|5=Bunrei|6=id|7=Kanjō|8=zh|9=分靈|10=fr|11=Kanjō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Invitation|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjō|qq=}}. It is also known as '''Sekison Daigongen''' or '''Oyama Sekison Daigongen'''.

