{{Infobox deity|venerated_in={{ill|Shugendō|qid=Q1483875}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q55528104]] Wikidata name: Sekison Gongen [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:10, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Sekison Gongen''' (石尊権現) is a deity of [[:en:Shinbutsu-shūgō|Shinbutsu-shūgō]] that emerged from the fusion of the [[:en:Mountain worship|Mountain Worship]] and [[:en:Shugendō|Shugendō]]-oriented beliefs of [[:en:Mount Ōyama (Kanagawa)|Oyama]], and enshrines [[:en:Ekādaśamukha|Eleven-Faced Kannon]] as its [[:en:Honji suijaku|Honji Buddha]]. It is often misunderstood because the [[:en:Honzon|Honzon]] of {{ill|Daisanji|ja|大山寺 (伊勢原市)|lt=Daisanji|lt_ja=大山寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daisanji|qq=|1=Ōyama-dera|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11434610}} was [[:en:Acala|Fudō Myōō]], but the [[:en:Honzon|Honzon]] of the Kannon-ji in {{ill|Monzen-machi|lt=Monzen-machi|lt=Monzen-machi|ja|門前町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Monzen-machi|qq=}} is the [[:en:Honji suijaku|Honji Buddha]].<ref name="#1">Daisan Chishi Chōsho (Tenpō 6)</ref> Before the implementation of [[:en:Shinbutsu bunri|Separation of Shinto and Buddhism]] and [[:en:Haibutsu kishaku|Haibutsu kishaku]], it was enshrined at Isurugi shrines nationwide after being invited from [[:en:Sagami Province|Sagami Province]] and {{ill|Amefuriyama Daisanji|ja|大山寺 (伊勢原市)|lt=Amefuriyama Daisanji|lt_ja=雨降山大山寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amefuriyama Daisanji|qq=|1=Ōyama-dera|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11434610}} via [[:en:Bunrei|Enshrinement]]. It is also known as '''Sekison Daigongen''' or '''Oyama Sekison Daigongen'''.
